Win.Dropper.LokiBot-9937195-0.description: Lokibot is an information-stealing malware designed to siphon off sensitive information stored on an infected device. It is modular in nature, supporting the ability to steal sensitive information from several popular applications. It is commonly pushed via malicious documents delivered via spam emails.

Win.Malware.Barys-9937004-0.description: This is a trojan and downloader that allows malicious actors to upload files to a victim's computer.

Win.Malware.Swisyn-9937249-0.description: Swisyn is a family of trojans that disguises itself as system files and services, and is known to drop follow-on malware on an infected system. Swisyn is often associated with rootkits that further conceal itself on an infected machine.

Win.Ransomware.TeslaCrypt-9937465-0.description: TeslaCrypt is a well-known ransomware family that encrypts a user's files with strong encryption and demands Bitcoin in exchange for a file decryption service. A flaw in the encryption algorithm was discovered that allowed files to be decrypted without paying the ransomware, and eventually, the malware developers released the master key allowing all encrypted files to be recovered easily.

Win.Trojan.Emotet-9937498-0.description: Emotet is one of the most widely distributed and active malware families today. It is a highly modular threat that can deliver a wide variety of payloads that is commonly delivered via Microsoft Office documents with macros, sent as attachments on malicious emails.

Win.Trojan.Gamarue-9937156-0.description: Gamarue, also known as Andromeda, is a botnet used to spread malware, steal information and perform activities such as click fraud.

Win.Trojan.Gh0stRAT-9937599-1.description: Gh0stRAT is a well-known family of remote access trojans designed to provide an attacker with complete control over an infected system. Capabilities include monitoring keystrokes, collecting video footage from the webcam, and uploading/executing follow-on malware. The source code for Gh0stRAT has been publicly available on the Internet for years, significantly lowering the barrier for actors to modify and reuse the code in new attacks.

Win.Virus.Xpiro-9937153-1.description: Expiro is a known file infector and information-stealer that hinders analysis with anti-debugging and anti-analysis tricks.

Win.Worm.Ruskill-9937238-1.description: Ruskill, also known as Dorkbot, is a botnet client aimed at stealing credentials and facilitating distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks. It spreads via removable media and through instant messaging applications.
